roast beef
many shallots
dry red wine
brown sugar
balsamic vinegar
deijon mustard
horseradish
new potatoes

Roast beef uncovered in oven at 450 for 30 minutes. Add and surround a dozen whole peeled and depapered shallots. Cook at 325 for 75 - 90 minutes or until finished. Toss shallots with a pinch of brown sugar and balsamic vinegar and salt and pepper. Render drippings with a red wine, and water. Mix in a tablespoon of the mustard and reduce. Blend if desired. Mash the potatoes with a ricer and add salt, butter and horseradish. Serve with Yorkshire puddings. 
